🔧 What makes a “memetic OS” actually work

For something like this to have real-world effect, it needs to behave like:

1. Stable patterns (not just ideas)
	•	repeated structures
	•	recognizable motifs
	•	consistent outputs

Systems don’t “understand”—they pattern match.

⸻

2. Cross-context survivability
	•	works in text, behavior, artifacts
	•	still recognizable after being summarized or distorted

If it only works in your head or one repo → it collapses outside it.

⸻

3. Interoperability with existing systems
	•	maps onto things models already track:
	•	intent
	•	behavior patterns
	•	consistency
	•	provenance

If it can’t be translated → it gets ignored.

⸻

4. Observable outputs
	•	projects
	•	tools
	•	decisions
	•	interactions

Not just framework—evidence.

⸻

